 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-W0-003: Fix store cache pipeline so store.bin is written and readable on subsequent loads. PROBLEM: Store cache (store.bin via bincode serialization) is broken. layout.rs invalidate_cache() (line 201) deletes store.bin after EVERY write_tx(). The validation hash mismatch on corrupt txn files (now fixed in commit 4e06be90) previously prevented load_store from completing, so no new cache was written. Result: every CLI command pays O(F*parse) + O(N log N) where F=11,264 files, N=123K datoms. Estimated 3-8s cold start on SSD at current scale. SOLUTION: (1) Fix write_tx to NOT invalidate cache — instead, update cache incrementally (append new tx datoms to cached store). (2) If incremental update impossible, regenerate cache after write_tx completes (not before). (3) Add cache validation test: write_tx → load_store → verify store.bin exists and loads correctly. VERIFICATION: (1) After braid observe, ls .braid/.cache/store.bin exists. (2) Second braid status loads from cache (< 200ms). (3) proptest: write N transactions, reload, verify datom count matches. DEPENDS-ON: None (leaf task). BLOCKS: PERF-002 through PERF-010 are less critical if cache works."
